# ── Allowlist repo ───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# This working folder holds far more than the published projects: raw data
# archives, legacy analyses, and scratch material — well over 1 GB, including
# individual files above GitHub's 100 MB hard limit. Tracking is therefore
# opt-in: everything at the root is ignored, and only the projects listed below
# are un-ignored. Add a new `!/name/` line to bring another one in.
#
# book-project is deliberately NOT tracked — it stays local. So is the
# top-level slides/ (the deck's authoring source); the site carries its own
# built copies under web-project/slides/.
#
# Note: these rules do not evict files git already tracks. When the repo root
# moved up, slides/ stayed tracked precisely because the parent holds files
# matching the old web-project-relative paths — it needed `git rm --cached`.
/*
!/.gitignore
!/.github/
!/web-project/
!/manuscript-modelos/

# ── Editor / OS / R session cruft ────────────────────────────────────────────
.DS_Store
**/.DS_Store
.Rproj.user
**/.Rproj.user/
.Rhistory
**/.Rhistory
.RData
.Ruserdata

# ── Quarto build output ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# `_freeze/` is deliberately NOT ignored: CI installs no R and renders the ENSO
# chunk from the committed freeze results under web-project/_freeze/.
**/.quarto/
**/*.quarto_ipynb
**/_site/
**/_book/
**/_manuscript/
**/*_files/

# Typst intermediate; the PDF beside it is committed on purpose.
manuscript-modelos/modelos.typ

# The manuscript project's freeze cache is local-only — nothing in CI reads it
# (only web-project/_freeze/ is needed for the published site).
manuscript-modelos/_freeze/

# ── Deliberately untracked ───────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Yellowfin-tuna reference material, unrelated to the jumbo squid work and not
# rendered by the site. This repo is public, so redistributing a third-party
# working paper here is a separate decision — kept local until it is made.
# Remove these two lines to include them.
web-project/docs/example_yft/
web-project/docs/wgpaper_iattc/SAC-11-INF-J_Yellowfin-tuna-risk-analysis-models-and-their-weights.pdf
